## Backend (FastAPI) layout

This project ships a FastAPI add-on under `app/`:

```
app/
  main.py       # FastAPI() instance + middleware stack + lifespan
  api.py        # APIRouter with sample routes (/healthz, /echo, /events/stream)
  services.py   # Pure-function business logic (also imported by app/cli.py)
  models.py     # Shared Pydantic models — single source of truth for HTTP + CLI
  settings.py   # pydantic-settings BaseSettings (reads .env)
  cli.py        # Typer CLI sibling (`uv run app-cli echo --message hi`)
{% if has_db %}  db.py         # SQLAlchemy async engine + sessionmaker
  schema.py     # Declarative Base + example User model
alembic/        # Async Alembic migrations (one initial revision)
{% endif %}tests/backend/  # pytest suite — unit, integration (Testcontainers), smoke
```

### Adding a route

1. Define request/response Pydantic models in `app/models.py`.
2. Add a route to `app/api.py` using those models.
3. Add a Typer command to `app/cli.py` using the SAME models (shares the schema).
4. Add a pytest in `tests/backend/`.

{% if has_db %}
### Adding a database model

1. Add the SQLAlchemy class to `app/schema.py`.
2. Generate a migration: `uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe it"`.
3. Apply: `uv run alembic upgrade head`.
{% endif %}

### Local stack

`just docker-up` brings up api + postgres + jaeger; `just docker-down` tears it down.
`just serve` runs uvicorn with auto-reload (no docker required, but no DB either).

### Verify

`just verify-backend` runs pytest + schemathesis fuzz + smoke against the live stack.
`just verify-backend-quick` runs pytest only (opportunistic fuzz when app already running).
`just verify` includes the `backend` check automatically when `has_backend=true`.

### Add-on flags

- `has_logfire={{ has_logfire }}` — Logfire auto-tracing for FastAPI, httpx, and LLM SDKs.
- `has_fastapi_mcp={{ has_fastapi_mcp }}` — every FastAPI route mounted as an MCP tool at `/mcp`.
- `has_db={{ has_db }}` — SQLAlchemy + asyncpg + Alembic.

